gw.api.system

Class PCConfigParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.system.PCConfigParameters

  • public class PCConfigParameters
extends java.lang.Object
    Used to fetch the values of configuration parameters defined in config.xml

    The list of parameters here is the list of all legal config parameters.

      • RateTableManagementNormalizationRowLimit

      • ParallelProductModelSyncTimeoutPerCoverable

        public static final IntegerParameterKey ParallelProductModelSyncTimeoutPerCoverable
        Number of milliseconds per coverable to wait for parallel product model sync. For example: when quoting a policy with 10 coverables and using the default timeout of 250ms per coverable, the server will time out the product model sync operation 2.5 seconds after it starts and display an error to the user. Disabling this timeout is not recommended as users may get stuck until the session times out. A value of -1 implies no timeout and the queue will wait until the product model sync completes or the session times out.

        public static final IntegerParameterKey AvailabilityContextCacheEntryExpirationTime
        LookupTableManager uses a cache to improve performance of Product Model availability lookups. Specific cache entries are expired after a period of inactivity, specified using this parameter (expressed in minutes). If a cache entry hasn't been accessed in the last X minutes, it will be expired from the cache so the beans and bundle can be garbage-collected by the VM.

        Default value: 1440 minutes (= 1 day) Min value: 1 minute Max value: 10080 minutes (= 1 week)

        public static final IntegerParameterKey RateTableCacheEntryLifetimeSecs

        It is recommended that this parameter and {#RateTableCacheUpdateIntervalSecs} are mutually prime, i.e., don't have any factors in common.

        The maximum this can be set to is 2592000 seconds or 30 days.

      • RateTableCacheUpdateIntervalSecs

        public static final IntegerParameterKey RateTableCacheUpdateIntervalSecs
        Time interval for periodically flushing or rebuilding the cache based on the RateTableCacheRebuildOnUpdate.

        It is recommended that this parameter and {#RateTableCacheEntryLifetimeSecs} are mutually prime, i.e., don't have any factors in common.

        The maximum this can be set to is 2592000 seconds or 30 days.

      • RateTableCacheRebuildOnUpdate

        public static final BooleanParameterKey RateTableCacheRebuildOnUpdate
        If true the RateTable cache is rebuilt at the update interval. If false, the RateTable cache is flushed.

        Rebuild recreates all rate table entries that are in the cache at the start of the update. No new rate tables are added to the cache by the rebuild. For internal use only and may be removed.
